About this item

  • HIGH QUALITY BLADE: Made of high quality stainless steel, robust, restaurant-grade blade engineered for years of use., slice fast and easy to use, just with little effort for cutting the potato, carrots, cucumbers, eggplant, onion into 1/2 inch thick strip.
  • ERGONOMIC HANDLE DESIGN: Extended handle makes everything easier to make homemade fries. With a single lever action you can squeeze through potatoes with ease.
  • NO NEED TO QUARTER OR HALF CUT THE POTATOES: The cutter box can takes 5.58*3.51inch potatoes, the capacity of this cutter is big enough for most potatoes, sweet potatoes and other vegetables. Cuts the entire potato in one go.
  • CONVENIENT FOR ALL: Cuts fries in 1/2" pieces. Also great for zucchinis, cucumbers and other vegetables, fruits into perfectly shaped sticks in seconds. Create stunning French fries, sweet potato fries, etc. For thinner 3/8 Inch blade, you may check the asin:B07MK28WBH.
  • SPACE SAVING AND EASY TO CLEAR: Unlike commercial French fry cutter in the market, which takes too much space, this potato cutter has small volume as well as commercial grade quality. Easy to clean with water, never be worried about rinsing and rust, use the cutter easily.

Product Description


Sopito is a professional brand manufacturer with rich experience in the kitchen, focus on the product itself is all in.

For many years, we have been committed to researching and manufacturing effort-saving french fry chopper cutter to provide people with fresh and nutritious potato chips.

Thoughtful features like ergonomic&compact design will make your time in the kitchen easier and more enjoyable.

Sopito Professional Potato Cutter

A Great Stainless Steel Fry Cutter For You!

Trying to avoid the unhealthy mixtures that pass for food lately? Are you looking to feed your family French fries they can trust?

Sopito Fry Cutter is the kitchen essential you have been looking for.

TIP:

1.lt's recommended to cut an edge on the end of the potato to make it easily to be cut off.

2.Microwave the sweet potatoes for a minute before cutting them.

3.If the suction cups do not work properly, place the cutter on a smooth counter like a marble tabletop, making sure to keep it dry.

  • Food-grade and Solid Material:Made of solid stainless steel, more durable and stable
  • Rolling Shaft Design:Reduce resistance, save your labor. Just cut potatoes easily and quickly
  • High-Quality Sharper Blade:Robust, restaurant-grade blade engineered for years of use. it won't bend or break when cutting high fiber foods like sweet potatoes, carrots etc.

UNSURPASSABLE CAPACITY

The capacity is 5.6 X 3.5 inch, exceed to hold the whole potato with ease, overpass most other cutters on the market

ERGONOMIC HANDLE DESIGN

Extended handle measures 11.5 inches/ 29cm long, designed for easy leverage so you never get sore while mashing.

SUPER SUCTION STRENGTH

More firmly adsorbed on the working mesa and no move during cutting

DURABLE AND MADE TO LAST

Made of 100% professional grade stainless steel that will last for years. Easy to cut dozens of potatoes without any damage.

YOUR AIR FRYER'S SIDEKICK

Works great with your AIRFRYER,DEEP FRYER OR OVEN for home-made gourmet healthy frenchfries.

FRESH AND HEALTHY FRIES

Now you can get fresh and restaurant-quality fries right at home! Prepare fries for a snack, party, or dinner with ease.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

But what truly sets this potato cutter apart is its simplicity and ease of use. With just a few quick motions, I can turn a whole potato into a pile of evenly-sized fries in seconds. It's incredibly satisfying to watch, and it saves me so much time and effort compared to cutting fries by hand.

James F
4.0 out of 5 stars "I'll take a side of fries with that."
Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2023
Size: 1/2 Inch & 3/8 InchVerified Purchase
First, I want to thank fellow user Brandon for his review at <<https://www.amazon.com/gp/aw/review/B09N366CB8/RJ6M6NFZMUDSO?ref_=cm_sw_r_apann_dprv_E9237EWPTQZ0EJ4ZV1P7>>. It gave me a better idea of what to expect. I have some physical limitations and based on other reviews would have thought this to be like a hot knife through butter. Having said that...
EASE OF USE:
This does require some strength to push it through. It was a little awkward for me at first, but after a couple of tries, got it through and it became easier.
ASSEMBLY FOR USE:
As for the assembly, putting it together is a cinch. Insert the round handle into the threaded end of the flat handle and tighten. Then, lay the device on its base (meaning the suction cup on the counter), pull the push mechanism all the way back, insert the flat handle with the bend pointing toward the blades, line up the holes in the handle with the holes in the mechanism, insert the screws, tighten them, and you're done.

MANUFACTURING ASSEMBLY:
For the unit itself, as one reviewer, Baby Mama (assuming it was Baby Papa in the video) noted in a video, it would be better if there were two suction cups, one on each end. I had some issues with it sliding on me while trying to push down to push the potato through. So, a suction cup on each end would be helpful, in my opinion. I just place a lightweight microfiber cloth under the other side where the blade is for helping stabilize that end.

The overall unit is sturdy, and I don't feel like it's going to just pop apart while pushing down.

It's relatively lightweight, comes with two different blades and corresponding pushers, which is great if you want to make different things (like French fries or zucchini fries).
This makes it incredibly easier than cutting by hand, and more precise. Previously, I was using a mandoline for the slices, then using a slice to gage the width of the sticks for the fries and it just felt too laborious. This streamlines the entire thing and is safer than the mandoline. (While I am an experienced mandoline user, the SNL horror show always runs through my mind while using it for some reason.)

One thing I did notice is this says it is designed for sweet potatoes, but I tried with a small piece of one instead of trying a whole one, since most potato cutters CANNOT properly cut them because of how tough they are. And this didn't seem to be able to do it, either. As I said, I have some physical strength issues, so maybe that is why, but I shouldn't need THAT much strength.

OVERALL:
I think this is a great product. It's at a reasonable price point for what you get. It's sturdy, relatively easy to use, and actually fulfills it's purpose. I'd definitely recommend it. But, I did have to take it down a star for, in my opinion, needing the second suction cup.

Thank you Sopito.

Amazon Customer
5.0 out of 5 stars Great Product, poor packaging *Updated*
Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
Size: 1/2'' BladeVerified Purchase
As a French fry maker this is amazing. It's now my favorite way to prepare potatoes.

HOWEVER I'm giving this three stars because of the poor packaging and shipping.

The package came to me in what looked the original box with loads of tape wrapped on it. The box was torn, ripped and severely damaged. Looks like the delivery company (UPS?) just wrapped about 10FT of tape around the box to prevent more things from falling out.

The French fry cutter came with missing parts due to this. It's missing bolts for the lever and the grip for the lever.

I could have said something to the seller, but didn't because it's still functional and I used spare bolts and nuts to make the lever work.

"BuT ThIs is An IsSuE with DelIvEry, NOT the SelLer!" I hear you say. Here's why I disagree:

This thing is mostly metal, at least 90% metal. The rest is small plastic fixtures and rubber.
Metal is heavy *duh* so more packaging needs to be made FOR the product BY the seller to protect the product.

Car parts are also made of mostly metal (mechanical anyway) and packaging for metal car parts involves ALOT of cardboard and foam. Not to protect the product, but to protect the box.

In short, again fantastic product. Would recommend. Just expect the box to be damaged at least a little bit. You're lucky if you don't have anymore than a small hole on the box when you get it.

Happy French fry making!

*Update* Customer service contacted me and asked what parts were missing. I only asked for the handle, I got it in the mail and it's much easier to cut potatoes now. 5 stars. Thank you!
